    "context": "Author: [github.com/lzl124631x](https://github.com/lzl124631x)\n\nMy C++ Code for LeetCode OJ.\n\nPlease give this repo a :star: if it inspires you. Thanks. :blush:\n\n😩 Hate manually copy & pasting the example testcases when solving LeetCode problems?  \n👉 Try my [LeetCode Testcase Extractor](https://liuzhenglai.com/post/5e6f2551e9a0d01760b274d8)\n\nNow I'm using a Chrome Extension I developed -- [LeetCoder](https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/gkmoalkjclphfhgnhdlilebaolpdkgpf) -- to facilitate my having fun on LeetCode. Features including but not limited to:\n* showing stats\n* copying problem, answer and **testcases**\n* randomly picking a problem.\n\n\\# | Title | Difficulty | Solution\n---|---|---|---\n1 | Two Sum | Easy | [Solution](leetcode/1)\n2 | Add Two Numbers | Medium | [Solution](leetcode/2)\n3 | Longest Substring Without Repeating Characters | Medium | [Solution](leetcode/3)\n4 | Median of Two Sorted Arrays | Hard | [Solution](leetcode/4)\n5 | Longest Palindromic Substring | Medium | [Solution](leetcode/5)\n6 | ZigZag Conversion | Medium | [Solution](leetcode/6)\n7 | Reverse Integer | Easy | [Solution](leetcode/7)\n8 | String to Integer (atoi) | Medium | [Solution](leetcode/8)\n9 | Palindrome Number | Easy | [Solution](leetcode/9)\n10 | Regular Expression Matching | Hard | [Solution](leetcode/10)\n11 | Container With Most Water | Medium | [Solution](leetcode/11)\n12 | Integer to Roman | Medium | [Solution](leetcode/12)\n13 | Roman to Integer | Easy | [Solution](leetcode/13)\n14 | Longest Common Prefix | Easy | [Solution](leetcode/14)\n15 | 3Sum | Medium | [Solution](leetcode/15)\n16 | 3Sum Closest | Medium | [Solution](leetcode/16)\n17 | Letter Combinations of a Phone Number | Medium | [Solution](leetcode/17)\n18 | 4Sum | Medium | [Solution](leetcode/18)\n19 | Remove Nth Node From End of List | Medium | [Solution](leetcode/19)\n20 | Valid Parentheses | Easy | [Solution](leetcode/20)\n21 | Merge Two Sorted Lists | Easy | [Solution](